<p></p>.<p>
The symptoms of acute sinusitis arise from inflammation of the lining tissues of the paranasal sinuses. This condition often occurs with <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/chronic_rhinitis/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">rhinitis</a> (inflammation of the lining of the nose), and symptoms can include</p>.<p>
Other symptoms that can be related to <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/sinusitis/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">sinusitis</a> 
and sinus <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/pain_management/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">pain</a> are</p>.<p>
Generalized symptoms like <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/fatigue/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">fatigue</a> are also typical.
</p>.<p>
<a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/sinusitis_pictures_slideshow/article.htm" rel="slide" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">Sinusitis</a> can be caused by infections, <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/allergy/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">allergies</a>, and chemical or other irritation of the sinuses. Both bacterial and viral infections such as the <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/common_cold/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">common cold</a> may lead to sinusitis. <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/dehydration/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">Dehydration</a>, disease, medications that lead to drying of the airways, and lack of sufficient humidity can cause sinusitis or <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/sinusitis/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">sinus infection</a>.
</p>.<p class="credits">REFERENCES:<br><br>
